author: @swastiknayak865
text: Response coding is one of the famous technique that people are using now a days sir. its totally works on probability. Lets say we have categorical feature name as  "STATE_NAME" which consists of all the state name of india and we have two target labels  as 0&1. So we can get the probability value by dividing each state_name with the particular label and the total occurance of that state. In this way we can calculate probability value of each state with respect to label. Here we are overcoming with the dimension problem that occured by doing one_hot_encoding and also we can get the exact particular value. You can correct me if i put something wrong.
